  <div class="column-two-thirds">
        <h1 class="part-title">
          How to apply
        </h1>
      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr rich-govspeak disable-youtube">
  <h2 id="new-students-from-england">New students from England</h2>

<p>Most full-time and part-time students can <a href="/apply-online-for-student-finance">apply online</a> to Student Finance England.</p>

<ol class="steps">
<li>
<p>Set up a student finance online account.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Log in and complete the online application.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Include your <a href="/apply-for-student-finance/household-income">household income</a> if needed. Your parent or partner will be asked to <a href="/support-child-or-partners-student-finance-application">confirm these details</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Send in <a href="/apply-for-student-finance/proof-of-identity">proof of identity</a>, if needed.</p>
</li>
</ol>

<div role="note" aria-label="Information" class="application-notice info-notice">
<p>If you can’t apply online, use the <a href="/student-finance-forms">form finder</a> to get the forms you need. You can <a href="/contact-student-finance-england">call Student Finance England</a> if you want to apply online but you can’t use a computer without help.</p>
</div>

<h2 id="continuing-students-from-england">Continuing students from England</h2>

<p>You’re a ‘continuing student’ if you got finance last year. <a href="/student-finance-register-login">Log in to your student finance account</a> and apply online.</p>

<p>There’s a different process if you became a part-time student <a href="/student-finance-for-existing-students">before 1 September 2012</a>.</p>

<h2 id="scotland-wales-and-northern-ireland">Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland</h2>
<p>There’s a different process for students from <a rel="external" href="http://www.saas.gov.uk/">Scotland,</a> <a rel="external" href="http://www.studentfinancewales.co.uk/">Wales</a> and <a rel="external" href="http://www.studentfinanceni.co.uk/">Northern Ireland</a>.</p>

<h2 id="new-eu-students">New <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> students</h2>

<ol class="steps">
<li>
<p>Download an application pack - use the <a href="/student-finance-forms">form finder</a> to get the forms you need.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Send in <a href="/apply-for-student-finance/proof-of-identity">proof of identity</a>, if needed.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>You’ll get a letter confirming how much you’ll get, usually within 6 weeks.</p>
</li>
</ol>

<h2 id="continuing-eu-students">Continuing <abbr title="European Union">EU</abbr> students</h2>

<p>If you’re a continuing student you’ll be sent the application forms.</p>


</div>

